        "Ingredients": "['4 tablespoons unsalted butter', '1 1-inch piece ginger, peeled, cut into thin matchsticks', '4 scallions, white and pale green parts finely chopped, dark green parts thinly sliced', '1½ pounds tomatoes, cut into 1-inch pieces (about 4 cups)', '2 tablespoons plus 1½ teaspoons white or regular soy sauce', 'Kosher salt']",
        "Instructions": "['Heat butter in a large skillet over medium. As soon as butter stops foaming, add ginger and scallion whites and cook, stirring, until fragrant, about 1 minutes. Add tomatoes and cook, turning gently with a large spoon, until tomatoes are juicy and just warmed through, about 2 minutes. Add soy sauce and toss to combine. Taste and season with salt, if needed. Top with scallion greens.Alex Lau']",
        "Image": "https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b5f17f0a6316e2d69db40f2/16:9/w_940,c_limit/healthyish-fmc-tomatotoastwide.jpg"
